    "# Goals {background-color=\"#2c3e50\"}\n",
    "\n",
    "## What We Will Cover\n",
    "\n",
    ":::: {.columns}\n",
    "::: {.column width=\"60%\"}\n",
    "1. **Define** what a differential equation is and what it means for a function to be a *solution*\n",
    "\n",
    "2. **Classify** ODEs by:\n",
    "   - order\n",
    "   - linearity / nonlinearity\n",
    "   - homogeneity\n",
    "   - constant vs. variable coefficients\n",
    "   - autonomy\n",
    "\n",
    "3. **Introduce** initial value problems (IVPs)\n",
    "\n",
    "4. **Survey** classical sources of ODEs in applications\n",
    ":::\n",
    "::: {.column width=\"40%\"}\n",
    "::: {.callout-note}\n",
    "This material corresponds to **Section 1.1** of @logan2015first.\n",
    ":::\n",
    ":::\n",
    "::::\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "# What Is a Differential Equation? {background-color=\"#2c3e50\"}\n",
    "\n",
    "## The Big Idea\n",
    "\n",
    "::: {.callout-important}\n",
    "## Key Point\n",
    "A **[differential equation](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Differential_equation)** is any equation involving an unknown **function** together with one or more of its **derivatives**.\n",
    "\n",
    "The goal is to find a *function* — not a number.\n",
    ":::\n",
    "\n",
    ". . .\n",
    "\n",
    "**Contrast with algebra:**\n",
    "\n",
    "| Type | Equation | Unknown |\n",
    "|---|---|---|\n",
    "| Algebraic | $x^2 - 4 = 0$ | a **number** $x = \\pm 2$ |\n",
    "| Differential | $\\dfrac{dy}{dx} = y$ | a **function** $y(x) = Ce^x$ |\n",
    "\n",
    ". . .\n",
    "\n",
    "::: {.callout-important}\n",
    "**Solutions to differential equations are functions, not numbers.**\n",
    ":::\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "## ODEs vs. PDEs\n",
    "\n",
    "**Ordinary Differential Equation (ODE)**\n",
    ": Involves a function of a **single** independent variable\n",
    "\n",
    "$$\\ddot{x} + \\omega^2 x = 0 \\quad \\leftarrow \\text{ one variable } t$$\n",
    "\n",
    ". . .\n",
    "\n",
    "**Partial Differential Equation (PDE)**\n",
    ": Involves a function of **several** independent variables\n",
    "\n",
    "$$u_t = k\\,u_{xx} \\quad \\leftarrow \\text{ two variables } x, t \\quad \\text{(heat equation)}$$\n",
    "\n",
    ". . .\n",
    "\n",
    "::: {.callout-note}\n",
    "In this course we focus **exclusively on ODEs**.\n",
    ":::\n",
    "\n",
    "Derivative notation is not standardized — see the footnote in the notes for the Leibniz, prime, dot, subscript, and operator conventions.[^deriv-notation]\n",
    "\n",
    "[^deriv-notation]: **Leibniz** $\\frac{dy}{dx}$; **prime (Lagrange)** $y', y'', y'''$; **dot (Newton)** $\\dot{x}, \\ddot{x}$ (time derivatives); **subscript** $u_x, u_{xx}$ (partials); **operator (Euler)** $Dy, D^2y$.\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "# Classifying ODEs {background-color=\"#2c3e50\"}\n",
    "\n",
    "## Order\n",
    "\n",
    "The **order** of an ODE is the order of the highest derivative present.\n",
    "\n",
    "| Equation | Order |\n",
    "|---|:---:|\n",
    "| $y' = ky$ | 1st |\n",
    "| $y'' + \\omega^2 y = 0$ | 2nd |\n",
    "| $y''' - y'' + y = \\sin t$ | 3rd |\n",
    "\n",
    ". . .\n",
    "\n",
    "General form of an $n$th-order ODE:\n",
    "$$F\\!\\left(t, y, y', y'', \\ldots, y^{(n)}\\right) = 0$$\n",
    "\n",
    "or solved for the highest derivative:\n",
    "$$y^{(n)} = f\\!\\left(t, y, y', \\ldots, y^{(n-1)}\\right)$$\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "## Linearity\n",
    "\n",
    "An ODE is **[linear](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Linear_differential_equation)** if it has the form:\n",
    "$$a_n(t)\\,y^{(n)} + \\cdots + a_1(t)\\,y' + a_0(t)\\,y = g(t)$$\n",
    "\n",
    "where the $a_k(t)$ and $g(t)$ depend **only on $t$**, not on $y$.\n",
    "\n",
    ". . .\n",
    "\n",
    "| Equation | Linear? | Reason |\n",
    "|---|:---:|---|\n",
    "| $y'' + 3y' - 2y = e^t$ | ✓ | Coefficients depend only on $t$ |\n",
    "| $y'' + \\sin(y) = 0$ | ✗ | $\\sin(y)$ is nonlinear in $y$ |\n",
    "| $y' = y^2$ | ✗ | $y^2$ is nonlinear in $y$ |\n",
    "| $t^2 y'' + ty' + y = 0$ | ✓ | Coefficients $t^2, t, 1$ depend only on $t$ |\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "## Homogeneity, Coefficients, Autonomy\n",
    "\n",
    "**Homogeneous** — forcing term $g(t) \\equiv 0$:\n",
    "$$a_n(t)\\,y^{(n)} + \\cdots + a_0(t)\\,y = 0$$\n",
    "\n",
    "**Inhomogeneous** — $g(t) \\not\\equiv 0$.\n",
    "\n",
    ". . .\n",
    "\n",
    "::: {.callout-tip}\n",
    "The general solution of an inhomogeneous linear ODE = *particular solution* + general solution of the homogeneous equation.\n",
    ":::\n",
    "\n",
    ". . .\n",
    "\n",
    "**Constant coefficients** — each $a_k$ is a constant number (not a function of $t$).\n",
    "\n",
    "**Variable coefficients** — at least one $a_k$ depends on $t$.\n",
    "\n",
    ". . .\n",
    "\n",
    "**Autonomous** — $t$ does not appear explicitly on the right-hand side:\n",
    "$$y' = f(y) \\;\\text{(autonomous)} \\qquad \\text{vs.} \\qquad y' = f(t,y) \\;\\text{(non-autonomous)}$$\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "## Classification Examples\n",
    "\n",
    "::: {.callout-note}\n",
    "## Example 1 — Logistic Equation\n",
    "$$\\frac{dP}{dt} = rP\\!\\left(1 - \\frac{P}{K}\\right)$$\n",
    "**1st-order, nonlinear, autonomous** — population growth with carrying capacity $K$.\n",
    ":::\n",
    "\n",
    ". . .\n",
    "\n",
    "::: {.callout-note}\n",
    "## Example 2 — Simple Harmonic Oscillator\n",
    "$$\\frac{d^2x}{dt^2} + \\omega^2 x = 0$$\n",
    "**2nd-order, linear, homogeneous, constant-coefficient, autonomous**\n",
    ":::\n",
    "\n",
    ". . .\n",
    "\n",
    "::: {.callout-note}\n",
    "## Example 3 — Driven Oscillator\n",
    "$$\\frac{d^2x}{dt^2} + 2\\gamma\\frac{dx}{dt} + \\omega^2 x = F_0\\cos(\\Omega t)$$\n",
    "**2nd-order, linear, inhomogeneous, non-autonomous, constant coefficients**\n",
    ":::\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "## Classification Examples (cont.)\n",
    "\n",
    "::: {.callout-note}\n",
    "## Example 4 — Euler's Equation\n",
    "$$t^2 y'' + t y' - 4y = 0$$\n",
    "**2nd-order, linear, homogeneous, variable (non-constant) coefficients**\n",
    ":::\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "# Solutions to ODEs {background-color=\"#2c3e50\"}\n",
    "\n",
    "## What Is a Solution?\n",
    "\n",
    "A **solution** of an ODE on an interval $I$ is a function $y = \\phi(t)$ that:\n",
    "\n",
    "1. Is differentiable (sufficiently many times) on $I$, **and**\n",
    "2. Satisfies the equation **for every** $t \\in I$.\n",
    "\n",
    ". . .\n",
    "\n",
    "::: {.callout-note}\n",
    "## Example 5 — General and Particular Solutions\n",
    "Consider $y' - 2y = 0$.  Check $y(t) = Ce^{2t}$:\n",
    "$$(Ce^{2t})' - 2(Ce^{2t}) = 2Ce^{2t} - 2Ce^{2t} = 0 \\checkmark$$\n",
    "\n",
    "- $y(t) = Ce^{2t}$ for any constant $C$ — **general solution** (one-parameter family)\n",
    "- With $y(0) = 3$: $C = 3$, so $y(t) = 3e^{2t}$ — **particular solution**\n",
    ":::\n",
    "\n",
    ". . .\n",
    "\n",
    "> A 1st-order ODE $\\to$ **one-parameter** family of solutions\n",
    "\n",
    "> A 2nd-order ODE $\\to$ **two-parameter** family, and so on.\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "## Visualizing the Family of Solutions"
